4.7 Actions Requiring Unanimous Board Approval. The Parties agree that the following matters require the approval of the Directors present at a Board meeting:
4.7.1 Revising operational guidelines of the Company;
4.7.2 Decisions related to the company's overall direction;
4.7.3 Entering into agreements or commitments with other parties.
